manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: MADE FOR NONSTICK COOKWARE 5-PIECE UTENSIL SET Take on a wide range of kitchen tasks with this ultra-versatile set from GreenPan. Crafted from silicone, these tools take on your daily tasks with ease. Mix, serve, stir, flip, mash, blend, scramble, and so much more! And don’t worry about your ceramic nonstick pots and pans. These utensils are designed for maximum scratch-free performance on ceramic nonstick surfaces. Each piece is dishwasher safe to make cleanup simple. FLEXIBLE SILICONE EXTERIORS STURDY METAL CORES These utensils have sturdy metal cores for stability and long-term use while retaining a handy flexibility at the edges, making them ideal for stirring, transferring, and mixing food. No matter what kitchen task you’re tackling, these tools ensure you’ll always be in total control. SCRATCH-FREE PERFORMANCE MADE FOR NONSTICK COOKWARE Each of these tools is specially designed to take on tough messes while maximizing performance on ceramic nonstick cookware. The silicone makes them extra flexible and the metal core makes them extra tough. MADE FOR DAILY COOKING DISHWASHER SAFE Designed for maximum durability and function, these tools can be popped in the dishwasher when you’re done, but most of the time they’ll wipe clean. MIX, MASH, BLEND, AND SO MUCH MORE! COVERS EVERY TASK Looking for the tools to take on your next kitchen challenge? These utensils have smooth, blemish-free surfaces, hold their color longer, and keep their shapes so you can cook with confidence.

Previous page HANDY TONGS Get a grip on your food with these metal and silicone tongs that are the ideals size for daily use. SILICONE TURNER Get underneath your food with the flexible tip and take control with the sturdy metal core. SILICONE SPATULA The smooth, flexible tip gets underneath your food and the metal core offers stability. SILICONE SKIMMER Perfect for removing foam or pulling dumplings, veggies, and fried food from pans. SLOTTED SPOON Get into tight corners, scrape your sauces, and strain easier with the flexible tip. Next page DURABILITY MEETS PERFORMANCE 1 Tongs 2 Turner 3 Spatula 4 Skimmer 5 Spoon

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I am very impressed with the durability and quality. They work perfect with my GreenPan cookware set that I got for Christmas. I will not use anything else. Great product and would highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These utensils are great!
reviews.reviewText: I recently bought a Greenspan set and wanted to make sure I was using the best utensils for them. These have been wonderful!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Not only are these low toxic, but they are easy to clean and cook with. My husband who loves to cook says that these are hands down the best utensils he used. Don't get him started on their pans! Their pans are the BEST also!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These silicone utensils are great. They are easy to hold , clean and do not scratch the pots and pans. Great product!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2023

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Hand wash only
reviews.reviewText: These utensils hang on to water spots from the dishwasher- to the point it almost makes them look gray. I’ll have to hand wash from now on- I would return but missed the return window by a few days.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Ughhh! Missing a large spoon
reviews.reviewText: Great except wish they included a large spoon in the set. Don’t need two straining spoons so has to buy separately a spoon to scoop food out quickly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Nicely constructed and I’m glad they won’t harm the finish on my new ”green pans” but the spoon is smaller than I expected and less useful on account of that.
